CREATE TABLE `bigquery-public-data.sdoh_bea_cainc30.fips`
(
  Year DATE OPTIONS(description="FIPS Year"),
  GeoFIPS STRING OPTIONS(description="US County Geoids"),
  GeoName STRING OPTIONS(description="US County Geoids Description"),
  Employer_contrib_pension_and_insurance INT64 OPTIONS(description="Thousands of dollars;Includes actual employer contributions and actuarially imputed employer contributions to reflect benefits accrued by defined benefit pension plan participants through service to employers in the current period."),
  Employer_contrib_govt_and_social_insurance INT64 OPTIONS(description="Thousands of dollars"),
  Farm_proprietors_income INT64 OPTIONS(description="Thousands of dollars"),
  Nonfarm_proprietors_income INT64 OPTIONS(description="Thousands of dollars"),
  Farm_proprietors_employment INT64 OPTIONS(description="Number of jobs; Excludes limited partners."),
  Income_maintenance_benefits INT64 OPTIONS(description="Thousands of dollars; Consists largely of Supplemental Security Income (SSI) payments; Earned Income Tax Credits (EITC); family assistance; general assistance; expenditures for food under the Special Supplemental Nutrition Program for Women, Infants, and Children (WIC); Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP); and other assistance benefits."),
  Nonfarm_proprietors_employment INT64 OPTIONS(description="Number of jobs"),
  Percapita_income_maintenance_benefits INT64 OPTIONS(description="Dollars; Type of income divided by population yields a per capita measure for that type of income."),
  Percapita_retirement_and_other INT64 OPTIONS(description="Dollars; Type of income divided by population yields a per capita measure for that type of income."),
  Percapita_unemployment_insurance_compensation INT64 OPTIONS(description="Dollars; Type of income divided by population yields a per capita measure for that type of income."),
  Proprietors_income INT64 OPTIONS(description="Thousands of dollars"),
  Retirement_and_other INT64 OPTIONS(description="Thousands of dollars"),
  Wages_and_salaries_supplement INT64 OPTIONS(description="Thousands of dollars"),
  Unemployment_insurance INT64 OPTIONS(description="Thousands of dollars"),
  Wages_and_salaries INT64 OPTIONS(description="Thousands of dollars"),
  Nonfarm_proprietors_income_avg INT64 OPTIONS(description="Dollars"),
  Wages_and_salaries_avg INT64 OPTIONS(description="Dollars"),
  Dividends_interest_rent INT64 OPTIONS(description="Thousands of dollars; Rental income of persons includes the capital consumption adjustment."),
  Earnings_by_place_of_work INT64 OPTIONS(description="Thousands of dollars"),
  Net_earnings_by_place_of_residence INT64 OPTIONS(description="Thousands of dollars"),
  Percapita_dividends_interest_rent INT64 OPTIONS(description="Dollars; Type of income divided by population yields a per capita measure for that type of income."),
  Percapita_net_earnings INT64 OPTIONS(description="Dollars; Type of income divided by population yields a per capita measure for that type of income."),
  Percapita_personal_current_transfer_receipts INT64 OPTIONS(description="Dollars; Type of income divided by population yields a per capita measure for that type of income."),
  Percapita_personal_income INT64 OPTIONS(description="Dollars; Type of income divided by population yields a per capita measure for that type of income."),
  Personal_current_transfer_receipts INT64 OPTIONS(description="Thousands of dollars"),
  Population INT64 OPTIONS(description="Number of persons; Census Bureau midyear population estimates. Estimates for 2010-2018 reflect county population estimates available as of March 2019."),
  Proprietors_employment INT64 OPTIONS(description="Number of jobs"),
  Wage_and_salary_employment INT64 OPTIONS(description="Number of jobs"),
  Earnings_per_job_avg INT64 OPTIONS(description="Dollars"),
  Personal_income INT64 OPTIONS(description="Thousands of dollars"),
  Total_employment INT64 OPTIONS(description="Number of jobs")
)
OPTIONS(
  description="FIPS Information Aggregated at the County Level",
  labels=[("freebqcovid", "")]
);
